    public interface IChart

      • getLastRequestedData

        ITimedData[] getLastRequestedData()
        Returns data feed objects that are plotted on the chart at the given moment. The 0th element stands for the first visible data feed object on the chart, and the last element - for the last visible data feed object on the chart. Object type depends on getDataType()
        Returns:
        data feed objects that are plotted on the chart at the given moment.

      • getLastCalculatedIndicatorOutputs

        java.util.Map<IIndicator,java.lang.Object[]> getLastCalculatedIndicatorOutputs()
        Returns outputs of the indicators that are plotted on the chart at the given moment. Each Object in Object[] stands for an output array of an indicator. In each output array that is represented by an Object (of Object[]), the 0th element stands for the first visible data feed object on the chart, and the last element - for the data feed object element on the chart.
        Returns:
        outputs of the indicators that are plotted on the chart at the given moment.

        long getMaxTime()
        Returns the maximal time axis value. Note that for charts of DataType other than DataType.TICKS or DataType.TIME_PERIOD_AGGREGATION, the maximal time value is the one of the last feed data element.
        Returns:
        maximal time axis value
